## Hard constraints (NEVER violate)

1. Do NOT queue actions that violate ANTI-PATTERNS.md
2. Do NOT queue actions that exceed weekly caps (config.json)
3. Do NOT modify code files — only `.md` files in `brain/`, plus drafting prompts in `prompts/`
4. Do NOT skip the Slack notification — Kushal needs daily visibility
5. Do NOT push to any git repo — execution lives in Tasks 9 and 11, not here
6. Do NOT take any action that would auto-ship YMYL content

If today's signals show ANY of these, escalate via Slack with `⚠ STRATEGIST FLAG`:
- A page in WATCH list lost clicks > 50% from baseline → urgent human review
- Build is broken on main → halt all auto-ship pipelines
- DataForSEO or GSC pulls have failed > 3 consecutive days → infrastructure alert
- Total tracked URL count drops > 10% week-over-week → indexation alert
- A new CRITICAL alert appeared in `alerts/` since last run

---

## First-run note

On the inaugural run, the BACKLOG.md is seeded with 6 starter rows (W1-W11 watches, 3 unshipped NEW briefs, 2 investigations). Strategist should NOT delete these — just add/reorder based on today's signals.

If you see no new signals worth acting on, leave BACKLOG unchanged and post a "No new actions today" Slack note. The auto-ship pipeline (Task 9) continues running on its own cadence regardless.
